## Abstract Summary
The dataset corresponds to research analyzing the effects of deep brain stimulation (DBS) in Parkinsonâ€™s disease (PD) through optogenetic fMRI in hemi-parkinsonian rats. It explores the underlying neural mechanisms and therapeutic potential of subthalamic nucleus (STN) DBS. The study provides insights into the neural targets and circuitry impacted by DBS, offering a nuanced understanding of its efficacy in managing motor symptoms in PD.

## Dataset Description
This dataset includes fMRI images, optogenetic stimulation parameters, and behavioral analysis results from hemi-parkinsonian rats subjected to subthalamic nucleus (STN) deep brain stimulation. It is organized according to the Brain Imaging Data Structure (BIDS) standard, facilitating easy use and interpretation.

## Usage Notes
Researchers intending to use this dataset should reference the associated publication for comprehensive methodology and findings. Please cite this work appropriately in any resulting publications and adhere to ethical guidelines for data usage.

